## Appendix B. Project-side bindings

The following values are **not** part of this rule — they belong in the consuming repo's `.cursor/rules/project/<name>-monorepo.mdc`:

- module-axis table (which boundary supports parallel splits in this repo)
- magnet-file list (concrete paths in this repo)
- test commands per stack (`npm test`, `pytest`, `go test ./...`, `cargo test --workspace`, ...)

If your repo lacks the binding file, start from `../examples/project-binding/monorepo-trunk-sample.md` (same folder layout as the fetched `coderules` pack; see README install paths) and replace every `<...>` placeholder.

## Appendix C. Failure modes this rule prevents

| Failure | Caught by |
|---|---|
| Agent B `git stash`-es agent A's uncommitted files | §0, §4 |
| Two agents both edit the same i18n / config file | §2, §3 |
| Agent A force-pushes over agent B's commits | §4 |
| Agent A's change breaks a contract agent B depends on | §5 |
| Merge commits accumulate, rebase becomes impossible | §4, §6 |
| Lockfile gets corrupted by parallel installs | §1 |
| Pre-existing scattered work gets buried in a new branch | §0, §8 |
| Nobody knows who is working on what | §7 |

